Mae Murray https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mae_Murray 0 Mae Murray (born Marie Adrienne Koenig, May 10, 1885 – March 23, 1965) was an American actress, dancer, film producer, and screenwriter. Murray rose to fame during the silent film era and was known as "The Girl with the Bee-Stung Lips" and "The Gardenia of the Screen".
